From 99251390089adc3c9159a0841db460cac0160986 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ethernova Patch <patch@ethernova.dev>
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 2026 12:10:47 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(adaptive-gas): skip gas adjustment during contract
 creation

ROOT CAUSE:
During contract deployment (tx.To == nil), evm.create() calls
run(evm, contract, nil, false) which executes init code (constructor).
The v1.1.0 patch blindly classified init code and applied gas adjustments.

Init code contains ABI-encoded constructor arguments as trailing raw
data bytes. Bytes like 0x54 (SLOAD) and 0x55 (SSTORE) in constructor
args get misinterpreted as opcodes by bytecode analysis, producing
inconsistent pureScore. Additionally, caching init code classification
under the contract address poisons the cache for subsequent runtime calls.

This caused: remote=36631 vs local=36373 -> invalid gas used -> BAD BLOCK

FIX:
1. Detect contract creation via input==nil (evm.create passes nil input)
2. Skip GlobalStaticClassifier.Classify() for init code (prevents cache poison)
3. Guard ApplyGasAdjustment() with !isContractCreation check
4. Add debug logging in state_transition.go for per-tx gas tracing
5. Add 3 new test functions for creation scenario coverage

Files changed:
- core/vm/interpreter.go (creation detection + skip adjustment)
- core/state_transition.go (tx gas trace logging)
- core/vm/adaptive_gas_test.go (3 new creation tests)
